article.headline: Valparaiso 76, Western Illinois 64
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Dan Oppland led four Crusaders in double figures and pulled down 10 rebounds as Valparaiso beat Western Illinois 76-64 Saturday night in a Mid-Continent conference game. The Leathernecks got within 60-59 with 3:43 left on a 3-pointer by David Jackson. But Ron Howard hit a layup to start a 16-3 run over the next 2:20 as Valparaiso stretched its lead to 14. Sammy Hunter, who finished with 21 for Western Illinois (7-17, 3-10 Mid-Con), hit a layup with 17 seconds left for the final margin. Mohamed Kone finished with 14 for the Crusaders (14-9, 7-6). Howard had 13 and Ali Berdiel scored 10. Jackson had 16 points and Fred Oguns 13 for the Leathernecks. Valpo outscored Western Illinois 38-18 in the paint and outrebounded the Leathernecks 44-33.
